The chair will be removed from its enclosure at Dearborn's Henry Ford Museum in Dearborn, Michigan, on April 15 as part of the museum's observance of the assassination's 150th anniversary .
On April 15, 1865, Abraham Lincoln was shot in Washington D.C. by pro-Confederacy actor John Wilkes Booth .
The chair has a dark stain on the back, which many visitors believe is from other people's heads who sat in the chair before Lincoln died .
It will be displayed in an open plaza on the Henry Ford Theater and displayed on display at the museum .